South Australia is blessed with some of the country's greatest natural wonders. Sunny weather with blue open skies are typical; grab a glass of its top quality red wine and enjoy amazing views with its warm#Comma friendly people.

Catching the ferry to windswept Kangaroo Island is an adventure in itself. Australia's third largest island is jam-packed full of natural beauty over a deceptively small place#Comma such as Seal Bay.

Located 110 km from Adelaide#Comma Auburn is the southern gateway to the rich vineyards of the Clare Valley and a once important town where bullock teams and miners stopped on their way from Port Wakefield to the copper mines around Burra.

Due the high influx of German immigrants#Comma this dish remains one of the MOST common dishes found in South Australia's cuisine.
Think spam and ham combined into a sausage "casing" and served like sliced ham at the delI#Comma because that's exactly what it tastes like.
Kitchener buns are essentially a big crusty#Comma flaky puff#Comma cut open#Comma smeared with a jam#Comma and filled with whipped cream.
